column128:
Adelphi University 



Principal Investigator: Dominic Fareri, Ph.D.

Research Purpose: The goal of this study is to begin to better characterize how our value of choice and decision-making is affected by social contexts.



Dear Participant,



Thank you for your participation. All of the photos you submitted have been deleted.



The study in which you have participated is part of a broader program of research aimed at understanding how differing social factors (e.g., being rejected or accepted by others; interacting with close vs. unknown others) affect our decision-making behavior and the value we place on our ability to make decisions (e.g., choosing for oneself or deferring the choice). Many of our day-to-day experiences occur when we are within some kind of social environment––i.e., in class with others, at home with our family, or at a social gathering with close friends and often leave us feeling either rejected or accepted. With the surge in technological advances and social media, how we experience social interactions has changed. In the task you performed, you were told that your photos were being shared with random partners who were going to give you feedback on your photos. In actuality, the partners in the task were computer-generated avatars that were pre-programmed to provide differing patterns of social feedback such that you experienced more acceptance or rejection from different partners. These responses were pre-programmed and were not actual evaluations of your photos from a real person. This was necessary to ensure similar experimental experiences across participants as well as to create an environment that closely simulated experiencing social rejection and acceptance. If you have additional questions, or are interested in the results of the study, please communicate with the research team via Prolific. In addition, if you decide that you wish for your data not to be used for this research, please let us know via messaging on Prolific and all of your data and records of your participation will be immediately and permanently destroyed.



Thank you again for your participation.
